article.description: — Noah Carter had 21 points and 12 rebounds as Northern Iowa beat Southern Illinois 74-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Carter scores 21 to lift N. Iowa past S. Illinois 74-62
article.linkText: Carter scores 21 to lift N. Iowa past S. Illinois 74-62
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- — Noah Carter had 21 points and 12 rebounds as Northern Iowa beat Southern Illinois 74-62 on Saturday. Bowen Born had 17 points for Northern Iowa (5-10, 3-6 Missouri Valley Conference), which snapped its five-game road losing streak. Trae Berhow added 16 points and seven rebounds. Austin Phyfe had 13 rebounds. Ben Harvey had 11 points for the Salukis (7-6, 1-6), whose losing streak stretched to six games. Kyler Filewich added 10 points. Dalton Banks had 10 points and six rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
